# ============================================================
# Trivy ignored findings (scan-root: infra/)
# ============================================================
# Findings here are accepted with documented architectural
# justifications. See docs/architecture/adr/.
# ============================================================

# AZU-0012: Storage account public network access
# Accepted on bootstrap state storage. Required for laptop-driven
# Terraform runs prior to VNet establishment. Mitigations include
# TLS 1.2 minimum, no anonymous access, soft delete, versioning.
# See ADR-001 for full reasoning.
AZU-0012

# AZU-0016: Key Vault purge protection
# Disabled in dev for fast iteration (allows immediate vault
# recreation without 7-day soft-delete window). Production
# environments enable via purge_protection_enabled = true,
# making this finding disappear naturally for them.
AZU-0016

# AZU-0057: Storage Analytics logging
# Accepted on bootstrap state storage. Diagnostic settings
# require Log Analytics which itself depends on this backend.
# Retrofitted in Week 5. See ADR-001.
AZU-0057

# AZU-0060: Customer-managed keys for storage
# Bootstrap state uses Microsoft-managed keys; consumer
# resources requiring stricter controls will use CMK from
# Key Vault. See ADR-001.
AZU-0060
